  "prompt": "I feel lost and I have lost faith in Islam, but not in God. Any advice or books I can read?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear you're struggling with your faith. Here are some suggestions that might help:\n\nBooks:\n1. \"Islam and the Destiny of Man\" by Gai Eaton\n2. \"The Heart of Islam\" by Seyyed Hossein Nasr\n3. \"Purification of the Heart\" by Hamza Yusuf\n4. \"Understanding the Hadith\" by Abdul Hamid Siddiqi\n5. \"No God But God\" by Reza Aslan\n\nAdvice:\n1. Speak with compassionate, open-minded scholars or counselors\n2. Join supportive Muslim communities that welcome honest discussions\n3. Study Islamic philosophy and mystical traditions like Sufism\n4. Focus on personal spiritual growth rather than rigid interpretations\n5. Remember that doubts are a natural part of spiritual journeys\n6. Explore the deeper meanings of Islamic teachings\n7. Practice self-compassion and patience with yourself\n\nOnline resources:\n- Seekers Guidance website\n- Yaqeen Institute for Islamic Research\n- Muslim Chaplains forums\n- YouTube channels of scholars like Omar Suleiman\n\nRemember that faith is a personal journey. It's okay to have questions and seek understanding. Your relationship with God is unique and valid.\n\nWould you like to discuss your specific concerns or challenges?",
